## Why this is powerful

Your tiny script just replaced the **planetary gear tabular method** that usually looks like this in textbooks:

```
member     motion
sun        +1
ring       −Nr/Ns
carrier    unknown
```

Instead you solved it using **linear algebra**.

That means your solver could easily handle:

```
compound planetaries
Ravigneaux
Simpson gearsets
Lepelletier transmissions
```

Which is exactly how **automatic transmissions** are modeled.

